      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The insistence on \"age-appropriate\" content often masks a lack of transparency regarding the actual curriculum being taught. Parents are right to demand evidence; schools should be required to provide clear, measurable outcomes demonstrating how these specific lessons improve a child's well-being, rather than just asserting their benefit. This calls for a stronger parental oversight mechanism to ensure that educational mandates align with established developmental and moral standards.",
      "source": "target",
